HEADWORD: Cuirassier
<hw>Cui`ras*sier"</hw> <pr>(kw?`r?s-s?r")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cuirassier</ets>. See <er>Curass</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A soldier armed with a cuirass; especially, a soldier of the
heaviest cavalry, wearing a cuirass only when in full dress.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
